metadata.name: Inner loneliness
metadata.description:
Artist: Ramazan Cirakoglu

Edition: 1/1

Collection: My Photo Arts

Photo Size: 4500x3000 pixel

Photo shoot date: 2020

About the photo: This man has retired from his job. He lost some people he loved very much and now lives alone. When he wakes up in the morning, he only sees himself in the mirror. Before going to bed, he sees only himself again. Despite everything, he is making a great struggle and holding on to life. This man lives in the Bilecik city, Turkey, in the village of Borcak, where the Ottoman empire was first born.
